-- GM to Cease Production of Astra Model at German Plant, FAZ Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-05-06T17:52:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/gm-to-cease-production-of-astra-model-at-german-plant-faz-says.html
General Motors Co. (GM)  plans to stop
making the Opel Astra model at its plant in the German town of
Ruesselsheim,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported, citing
unidentified people close to labor-union officials.  The decision to build the next generation of the car only
at facilities in England and Poland starting in 2015 will be
announced in mid-May, the newspaper said, citing the people, who
said they were aware of comments on the matter by Steve Girsky,
